Name: Address
Description: Street address of a single or multi-line address.

Name: Citizenship
Description: Citizenship is a relationship between an individual and a state to which the individual owes allegiance and in turn is entitled to its protection. Recognition by a state as a citizen generally carries with it recognition of civil, political, and social rights which are not afforded to non-citizens.

Name: Credit Card Network
Description: A string representing the network a credit card belongs to; Master Card, Visa, American Express, Discover etc.

Name: Day
Description: A string representing the days of the week that a shift worker has been granted time off. Each day is separated by a comma. For example, Monday, Tuesday.

Name: Education Status
Description: A string representing the level of education an individual has achieved.

Name: Hour
Description: A string representing a numeric value related to the hour of the day; 1-24.

Name: Income
Description: The total amount of money that a person receives, on a regular basis for work or through investments.

Name: Postal Code
Description: A postal code (also known locally in various English-speaking countries throughout the world as a postcode, post code, PIN or ZIP Code) is a series of letters or digits or both, sometimes including spaces or punctuation, included in a postal address for the purpose of sorting mail.

Name: National Identifier
Description: A national identification number, national identity number, or national insurance number is used by the governments of many countries as a means of tracking their citizens, permanent residents, and temporary residents for the purposes of work, taxation, government benefits, health care, and other governmentally-related functions. For example; US Social Security Number, Canadian Social Insurance Number (SIN), French INSEE Number, UK National Insurance Number, Spanish Fiscal Identification Number etc.

Name: Phone Number
Description: Phone Number is a string of specific numbers that a telephone or cell phone user can dial to reach another telephone or mobile phone independent of country.

Name: Quarter
Description: A string representing one quarter of a given year; Q1, Q2, Q3, Q4.

Name: Residence
Description: The residential living status of a person. For example, valid values would be; Owner Occupied, Public Housing, Private Housing, Renting, Sheltered, Living with parents/guardian etc.

Name: State/Province Code
Description: Two-letter alphabetic codes that are used to identify a country states or providences.

Name: Year
Description: A string or integer value representing a year; 1956, 2021 etc.
